summary: Marvel's Phase 3 so far has had four billion-dollar hits (Civil War, Black Panther, Infinity War and Captain Marvel) and we...
body: Marvel’s Phase 3 so far has had four billion-dollar hits (Civil War, Black Panther, Infinity War and Captain Marvel) and we haven’t even gotten to Endgame yet. I want to say that I don’t think they can really top this in Phase 4 but then I remember they now have film rights to the Fantastic Four and X-Men.

title: El último cameo de Stan Lee sería en Avengers: Endgame

title: Question.
body:
To any of my fellow writers/authors/people who write things,

I have this thing where I get REALLY emotionally invested into fics or certain characters and their arcs that I write. Then, when I write something sad that involves them, I feel like I’m putting an actual human being through that treatment, and I fall into a short depressive episode. Like, I full on weep over this. Is that normal? Does anyone else feel that way? Is it just me?

Me, putting characters I love through the wringer dozens of times for the sake of their story arc:
